               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r"/>-88v: Miracles of Mary. F<locus target="#1r"/>-17r: Vision of John, Son of Thunder, on the Dual Virginity of Mary, ራዕየ፡ ተአምር። ዘዮሐንስ፡ ወልደ፡ ነጐድጓድ፡. For a critical edition and English translation, see Getatchew Haile, The Mariology of Emperor Zär’a Ya‘ǝqob of Ethiopia, OCA 242 (Rome: Pontificium Institutum Studiorum Orientalium, 1992), esp. 70–93. F<locus target="#19r"/>-22r: Introductory reading to the Miracles of Mary on Sunday. F<locus target="#22v"/>-24v: Introductory Daily Reading to the Miracles of Mary. F<locus target="#25r"/>-88vSeventy-Six Miracles of Mary (the numbering is occasionally off).  F. i r mentions a secondary owner, ገብረ ሰንባት. F. ii v and iv r(ecto): Record of land given to the priest who work in the church. <locus target="#17r"/> mentions the scribe, ገብረ ሚካኤል. <locus target="#19r"/>: record, colophon: The year is 5,500 year (of the world), 1900EC, in the reign of ደግማዊ ምኒልክ, in the time of bishop ማቴዎስ, written in the monastery of Jesus, i.e., ምሑር በገዳመ ኢየሱስ. <locus target="#25r"/> mentions the abbott of the monastary, ገብረ ማርያም. </summary>
